01:11.165 --> 01:14.934
So I... I'm supposed to fly
to London tomorrow,

01:14.936 --> 01:18.538
but someone's passed away,
and I need to change my plans.

01:18.540 --> 01:20.106
Yeah, I'll hold.

01:20.108 --> 01:21.975
Let's just move
Jill's nephew to next week.

01:21.977 --> 01:24.177
Luke starts camp next week.

01:24.179 --> 01:27.213
Okay, then, uh... you see Luke,

01:27.215 --> 01:29.015
and we'll just move the Grants
to next week.

01:29.017 --> 01:31.050
The Grants are leaving
for Hawaii this weekend.

01:31.052 --> 01:32.919
Wow, okay, so why don't...

01:32.921 --> 01:34.888
there's the, um...

01:34.890 --> 01:36.156
this is harder than Sudoku.

01:36.158 --> 01:37.724
Can't Dr. Van Dyke fill in again?

01:37.726 --> 01:38.992
He wasn't Hankmed material.

01:38.994 --> 01:40.260
No follow-through.

01:40.262 --> 01:42.529
You know, if I'd had more time
to mentor him,

01:42.531 --> 01:44.297
yeah, he could've become
a world-class concierge doctor...

01:44.299 --> 01:46.399
Yeah, hi, I need to postpone my flight.

01:46.401 --> 01:48.801
No, please don't put me on hold again.

01:48.803 --> 01:50.436
Or just do it anyway.

01:50.438 --> 01:52.639
Babe, you didn't even know him,

01:52.641 --> 01:53.740
so you don't have to be there.

01:53.742 --> 01:55.875
Are you gonna be there?

01:55.877 --> 01:58.411
- Yeah.
- Then so will I.

01:58.413 --> 01:59.546
Yes, hi, I'm here.

01:59.548 --> 02:01.147
Okay, why don't you just tell me

02:01.149 --> 02:02.549
which clients are in town next week.

02:02.551 --> 02:03.883
Okay, I am talking... yeah,

02:03.885 --> 02:05.118
the... the red-eye Friday could work.

02:05.120 --> 02:07.787
What are you guys doing?

02:07.789 --> 02:10.089
We're, uh, just changing
some plans around.

02:10.091 --> 02:11.491
Why?

02:14.495 --> 02:18.531
Well... you took
a two-hour walk yesterday,

02:18.533 --> 02:19.899
and an even longer one
this morning, so...

02:19.901 --> 02:21.534
So?

02:21.536 --> 02:24.404
Henry, I didn't know Jack
very well, but I know you.

02:24.406 --> 02:26.439
I know what you're feeling right now,

02:26.441 --> 02:29.509
and I know why, so...

02:29.511 --> 02:31.344
Just let me handle everything.

02:31.346 --> 02:32.946
Seriously. At least till
after the funeral.

02:32.948 --> 02:35.315
First of all, Evan, I don't
need you to handle anything,

02:35.317 --> 02:39.085
and second of all,
there won't be any funeral.

02:39.087 --> 02:40.820
I checked with Jack's attorney,

02:40.822 --> 02:42.622
and Jack's attorney checked Jack's will.

02:42.624 --> 02:45.225
It specified that
he didn't want a funeral.

02:45.227 --> 02:47.360
Well, I guess that does sound like Jack.

02:47.362 --> 02:49.429
The will prohibited moping too.

02:49.431 --> 02:50.430
Hmm? Hmm?

03:00.507 --> 03:01.774
This is Hank.

03:01.776 --> 03:03.076
How can I make you feel better today?

03:18.092 --> 03:20.660
Bobby not able to push out.

03:20.662 --> 03:22.495
It's okay, Mrs. Sesumi. It's okay.

03:22.497 --> 03:25.398
Let me just take a look.

03:25.400 --> 03:28.034
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

03:28.036 --> 03:31.304
Whoa. Okay.

03:31.306 --> 03:32.772
Can you guys tell me how he did it?

03:34.876 --> 03:37.210
We were just making our little movie

03:37.212 --> 03:39.379
down in the woods.
Uh, we took a lunch break,

03:39.381 --> 03:41.614
and the next thing we knew,
Bobby was sucking face

03:41.616 --> 03:43.216
with this chocolaty beverage.

03:43.218 --> 03:44.350
Shut up!

03:44.352 --> 03:46.486
I'm Devon. Uh, I got your number

03:46.488 --> 03:47.754
from my friend Tucker Bryant.

03:47.756 --> 03:51.124
9-1-1. We ambulance ride for Bobby?

03:51.126 --> 03:52.225
We don't need an ambulance, okay?

03:52.227 --> 03:53.760
If I can break the suction,

03:53.762 --> 03:55.795
I should be able
to remove Bobby's tongue.

03:55.797 --> 03:58.197
Hold that, Bobby? Okay.

04:04.338 --> 04:09.175
Okay, I'm gonna anesthetize
the inside of your mouth.

04:09.177 --> 04:10.810
- Mm!
- All right.

04:10.812 --> 04:13.613
I know it pinches a little bit.

04:13.615 --> 04:16.349
- Ow!
- Okay.

04:16.351 --> 04:17.950
Good job, bud.

04:27.061 --> 04:30.763
Here we go.

04:30.765 --> 04:33.333
One, two, three.

04:36.170 --> 04:37.904
- Ah!
- I know, I know.

04:37.906 --> 04:40.540
There we go. Okay, okay.

04:40.542 --> 04:41.808
That's in.

04:49.650 --> 04:53.353
That's it. There we go.

04:53.355 --> 04:56.089
- Okay.
- Thank you.

04:56.091 --> 04:58.758
- Thank you.
- Okay, Mrs. Sesumi, okay.

04:58.760 --> 05:01.861
Bobby.

05:01.863 --> 05:05.331
So, uh, which one of you is older?

05:06.734 --> 05:08.768
I'm the ranking brother here.

05:08.770 --> 05:11.003
That's a big title, Devon.

05:11.005 --> 05:12.705
That means it's your job
to take better care

05:12.707 --> 05:15.208
of your little brother.
'Cause I'd really rather

05:15.210 --> 05:17.477
not be back here this weekend.

05:17.479 --> 05:18.478
Got it?

05:19.947 --> 05:22.882
- Got it.
- Okay.

05:22.884 --> 05:25.151
- That was perfect.
- Yeah.

05:28.222 --> 05:29.455
- Nina.
- Hey.

05:29.457 --> 05:31.157
- Hey.
- Hank.

05:31.159 --> 05:33.126
Um... did you get my messages?

05:33.128 --> 05:35.795
Uh, yeah, I did, I did.
I'm sorry for not calling back.

05:35.797 --> 05:37.730
Well, I, um... I just... I thought maybe

05:37.732 --> 05:40.266
you might wanna... debrief.

05:40.268 --> 05:41.434
You mean talk?

05:41.436 --> 05:43.803
Yeah. I mean talk.

05:43.805 --> 05:46.572
- You okay?
- Yeah.

05:46.574 --> 05:48.841
Yeah, I mean, it's... it's never easy

05:48.843 --> 05:50.943
with... with someone so young

05:50.945 --> 05:54.614
and full of life. And you?

05:54.616 --> 05:57.049
Yeah, yeah. I'm working through it.

05:57.051 --> 06:02.188
Hank, you did everything you could.

06:02.190 --> 06:05.425
Yeah, then I guess
there's not much to, uh...

06:05.427 --> 06:06.526
debrief about.

06:06.528 --> 06:08.161
Sorry, I gotta run.

06:08.163 --> 06:09.796
But I'll give you a call later.

06:44.598 --> 06:45.698
Oh.

06:45.700 --> 06:46.899
Can I help you?

06:46.901 --> 06:50.136
No, sorry. I'm good.

